# 1. 今日はついに

Kohane & Miku: ————♪ ————♪
An, Akito & Toya: ——————...♪
Kohane: (Alright, we sound pretty good.)
Kohane: (I'm glad we asked Taiga and the others about places near our hotel where we can sing.)
Kohane: (And singing somewhere different has a nice sense of freshness to it...)
Kohane: (But...)
Kohane: (This still isn't good enough.)
Kohane: (We need our voices to really resonate!)
Kohane: ♪——————————~~~!!
Akito: Alright, we'll go get some drinks.
An: We'll buy some for you guys, too, so sit tight!
Toya: Alright. Thank you both.
Kohane: Thanks for helping us practice, Miku.
Miku: <Not a problem. I had a lot of fun singing with you. I have to say, though...>
Miku: <You seem extra motivated today, Kohane.>
Kohane: Huh?
Toya: I felt it too. Your voice is always powerful, but you seem to be really channeling your feelings today.
Kohane: My feelings...
Kohane: I suppose so. I do believe that I need to keep trying harder.
Kohane: Especially considering what happened in SEKAI the other day.
Toya: Are you referring to the dream those black fragments showed us?
Kohane: Yeah. In that dream, the four of us were totally separated. It really drove home that...
Kohane: I need to treasure the time we get to sing together. Because I want to stand on top of the world, the four of us, together.
Miku: <I see. It sounds like that experience is really spurring you on.>
Kohane: Yeah!
Kohane: That said... I still don't really know what it means to “stand on top of the world”.
Toya: It is a massive goal. It's difficult to picture it clearly.
Miku: <I agree. But there's no need to rush to find an answer.>
Kohane: Huh?
Miku: <I mean, you're all still discovering your new dream, right?>
Miku: <You'll visit new places and experience new things in the future, so I think it's okay for you to all figure things out as you go along.>
Miku: <And eventually, you'll find what “standing on top of the world” means to you.>
Toya: Right. For now, let's focus on doing what we can.
Kohane: Yeah... And we're seeing Taiga's event today.
Kohane: Maybe we'll pick something up there!
Toya: Taiga...
Miku: <Is something the matter, Toya?>
Toya: No, it's just... Ken has watched and helped us practice.
Toya: But we haven't heard Taiga sing since that time we battled against him.
Kohane: Oh...
Taiga: ♪————————————!!
Kohane: Right...
Kohane: (Taiga seemed so insurmountable then.)
Kohane: (I didn't know if we'd ever be able to overcome him. I was afraid to even try. But now...)
Kohane: It's funny, isn't it?
Miku: <What is?>
Kohane: Back then, I never would've imagined everything that's happened.
Kohane: After hearing Taiga sing, I was so scared we might not actually be able to surpass RAD WEEKEND.
Kohane: But we trained like nothing else mattered, and we managed to break through that enormous wall. And now...
Kohane: Here we are, in real life.
Toya: Yes, there was never a dull moment. It's almost dizzying in retrospect...
Miku: <You really have been through a lot.>
Kohane: Yeah... But we've gotten to see and do so many different things. And we've grown so much as a result.
Kohane: So...
Kohane: I'm really looking forward to what we're going to see next, starting with the event today!
Toya: Me too. We should enjoy what the world's stage has to offer us.
Miku: <Come to think of it, what's today's event going to be like? You said that it's supposed to be really big.>
Toya: It's called “SONIC NOTES”. It's still a relatively new event, so we don't know much about it either.
Toya: But after a world-class label became a sponsor last year, the event has absolutely exploded in prestige and lineup both.
Kohane: Artists from around the world are going to perform, right? I can't wait!
An: We're back! We got water for everyone.
Kohane: Oh, welcome back, you two!
Akito: Sorry about the wait. Here's yours.
Toya: Thank you. Let's resume practice after you two have had a chance to rest.
Kohane: Oh, in that case, can I sing while you guys take your break?
Kohane: I came up with a new arrangement for that part we just practiced, and I really want to give it a try.
Akito: Sure. Then, we'll listen.
Kohane: Thanks! Here it goes...
Kohane: ♪————————
???: *Sigh* “Thank goodness I was able to snag some ice cream♪”
???: “I don't know how you can eat that stuff so early in the morning. Don't come crying to me later if you get a stomachache.”
???: “I'll be fine! Let's go home so I can eat this.”
Kohane's Voice: ♪...——————
???: “Oh, someone's singing over there.”
???: “Look at that. Not many people are out this early...”
Kohane: ♪——————~~...
???: “Hey, she's really good! I wanna talk to her!”
???: “Yes, she has a nice voice. And she seems very skilled...”
???: “Hmm... But you really shouldn't interrupt her.”
???: “Because I know you're going to ask to sing with her, Elena. And if you do, your ice cream's going to melt.”
???: “What?! I wouldn't... No, I would...”
???: “But I really feel like singing now! So, why don't we sing together later?”
???: “Hmm... Okay, after we get home, and you have your ice cream. It's been a little bit, so why don't we hit up you-know-where?”
???: “Yay! I'll make quick work of it♪”
